## Plan Summary

**Bug found:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```typescript
// Current (buggy)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// Fixed
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The `- 1` makes the loop stop before reaching the last index. For a 1-element array the loop body never runs at all (`i < 0` is immediately false). For larger arrays, only the last element is dropped.

**The fix:** Remove `- 1` from the condition on line 7 of `src/utils.ts`. That's the only change needed — the tests in `tests/utils.test.ts` already cover all the affected cases and will pass once the fix is applied.

